1
00:00:07,583 --> 00:00:09,917
Katara: WATER...

2
00:00:09,959 --> 00:00:11,417
EARTH...

3
00:00:11,458 --> 00:00:13,542
FIRE...

4
00:00:13,583 --> 00:00:16,083
AIR.

5
00:00:16,125 --> 00:00:17,792
LONG AGO...

6
00:00:17,834 --> 00:00:19,750
THE FOUR NATIONS LIVED
TOGETHER IN HARMONY.

7
00:00:19,792 --> 00:00:24,500
THEN EVERYTHING CHANGED
WHEN THE FIRE NATION ATTACKED.

8
00:00:24,542 --> 00:00:28,583
ONLY THE AVATAR,
MASTER OF ALL FOUR ELEMENTS
COULD STOP THEM.

9
00:00:28,625 --> 00:00:30,208
BUT WHEN THE WORLD
NEEDED HIM MOST

10
00:00:30,250 --> 00:00:32,375
HE VANISHED.

11
00:00:32,417 --> 00:00:36,125
100 YEARS PASSED AND MY BROTHER
AND I DISCOVERED THE NEW AVATAR

12
00:00:36,166 --> 00:00:38,125
AN AIRBENDER NAMED AANG.

13
00:00:38,166 --> 00:00:40,250
AND ALTHOUGH HIS AIRBENDING
SKILLS WERE GREAT

14
00:00:40,291 --> 00:00:43,542
HE HAS A LOT TO LEARN BEFORE
HE'S READY TO SAVE ANYONE.

15
00:00:43,583 --> 00:00:47,750
BUT I BELIEVE AANG
CAN SAVE THE WORLD.

16
00:00:47,792 --> 00:00:49,542
♪

17
00:00:55,041 --> 00:00:57,125
Ozai: I AM PROUD OF YOU,
PRINCE ZUKO.

18
00:00:57,166 --> 00:01:00,166
YOU SLAYED THE AVATAR.

19
00:01:00,875 --> 00:01:03,583
Zuko: YOU'RE SO BEAUTIFUL
WHEN YOU HATE THE WORLD.

20
00:01:03,625 --> 00:01:05,500
I DON'T HATE YOU.

21
00:01:05,542 --> 00:01:06,750
I DON'T HATE YOU, TOO.

22
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:11,500
I HAVE EVERYTHING
I ALWAYS WANTED.

23
00:01:11,542 --> 00:01:13,583
BUT IT'S NOT AT ALL
HOW I THOUGHT IT WOULD BE.

24
00:01:13,625 --> 00:01:16,125
THE AVATAR IS ALIVE.

25
00:01:16,166 --> 00:01:17,709
I WANT YOU TO FIND HIM...

26
00:01:17,750 --> 00:01:19,625
...AND END HIM.

27
00:01:22,041 --> 00:01:25,959
♪

28
00:01:28,041 --> 00:01:30,000
[GROWLS]

29
00:01:30,041 --> 00:01:33,291
Ty Lee: I'M SO EXCITED TO SPEND
THE WEEKEND ON EMBER ISLAND.

30
00:01:33,333 --> 00:01:36,709
IT'S GONNA BE GREAT TO HANG OUT
ON THE BEACH AND DO NOTHING.

31
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:38,458
DOING NOTHING
IS A WASTE OF TIME.

32
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:40,583
WE'RE BEING SENT AWAY
ON A FORCED VACATION.

33
00:01:40,625 --> 00:01:41,875
I FEEL LIKE A CHILD.

34
00:01:41,917 --> 00:01:43,625
LIGHTEN UP.

35
00:01:43,667 --> 00:01:45,083
SO DAD WANTS TO MEET
WITH HIS ADVISORS ALONE

36
00:01:45,125 --> 00:01:46,709
WITHOUT ANYONE ELSE AROUND.

37
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:48,458
DON'T TAKE IT PERSONALLY.

38
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,375
DOESN'T YOUR FAMILY HAVE
A HOUSE ON EMBER ISLAND?

39
00:01:51,417 --> 00:01:53,208
WE USED TO COME EVERY
SUMMER WHEN WE WERE KIDS.

40
00:01:53,250 --> 00:01:55,083
THAT MUST'VE BEEN FUN.

41
00:01:55,125 --> 00:01:57,375
THAT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

42
00:02:09,125 --> 00:02:12,041
Both: WELCOME TO
EMBER ISLAND, KIDS.

43
00:02:24,041 --> 00:02:26,166
IT SMELLS LIKE
OLD LADY IN HERE.

44
00:02:26,208 --> 00:02:27,709
GEE, I WONDER WHY.

45
00:02:30,458 --> 00:02:32,333
Ty Lee: WHO ARE THESE
TWO BEAUTIFUL WOMEN?

46
00:02:32,375 --> 00:02:36,083
CAN'T YOU TELL?

47
00:02:36,125 --> 00:02:38,041
IT'S LI
AND ME.
[RETCHES]S LO AND ME.

48
00:02:38,083 --> 00:02:41,208
OOH, I LOVE
THIS SEASHELL BEDSPREAD.

49
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:43,000
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

50
00:02:43,041 --> 00:02:45,208
IT LOOKS LIKE THE BEACH
THREW UP ALL OVER IT.

51
00:02:45,250 --> 00:02:47,291
Li: WE KNOW YOU'RE UPSET

52
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:50,250
THAT YOU WERE FORCED
TO COME HERE THIS WEEKEND.

53
00:02:50,291 --> 00:02:53,208
BUT EMBER ISLAND
IS A MAGICAL PLACE

54
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:55,166
KEEP AN OPEN MIND.

55
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:57,709
GIVE IT A CHANCE.

56
00:02:57,750 --> 00:03:00,834
AND IT CAN HELP YOU UNDERSTAND
YOURSELVES AND EACH OTHER.

57
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:05,959
THE BEACH HAS
A SPECIAL WAY

58
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,125
OF SMOOTHING EVEN
THE MOST RAGGED EDGES.

59
00:03:08,166 --> 00:03:10,709
[YAWNS]

60
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:13,250
Both: TIME TO HIT THE BEACH.

61
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:19,625
Toph: AANG, I KNOW
SWIMMING IS FUN AND ALL

62
00:03:19,667 --> 00:03:22,125
BUT DO YOU REALLY
THINK YOU SHOULD BE
EXPOSING YOURSELF LIKE THAT?

63
00:03:22,166 --> 00:03:23,083
COVER UP.

64
00:03:23,125 --> 00:03:24,083
WHAT?

65
00:03:24,125 --> 00:03:26,208
I'M WEARING TRUNKS.

66
00:03:26,250 --> 00:03:27,667
I KNOW, IT'S YOUR TATTOOS
I'M WORRIED ABOUT.

67
00:03:27,709 --> 00:03:29,500
WHAT IF SOMEONE SEES YOU?

68
00:03:29,542 --> 00:03:31,000
THERE ARE WALLS
ALL AROUND US.

69
00:03:31,041 --> 00:03:32,417
IT'S COMPLETELY SAFE.

70
00:03:32,458 --> 00:03:34,667
[CHIRPS]

71
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:38,750
Aang: WHOO, HEY!

72
00:03:38,792 --> 00:03:41,792
[MOMO CHIRPS]

73
00:03:41,834 --> 00:03:45,500
[LAUGHING]

74
00:03:45,542 --> 00:03:49,792
THIS HAS GOT TO BE THE MOST
BORING JOB IN THE FIRE NATION.

75
00:03:49,834 --> 00:03:50,834
NOTHING EVER HAPPENS.

76
00:03:50,875 --> 00:03:52,500
[SNIFFS]

77
00:03:52,542 --> 00:03:54,417
Aang: WHOA!

78
00:03:56,959 --> 00:03:58,417
LET'S GO AGAIN.

79
00:04:04,542 --> 00:04:06,583
THE AVATAR'S ALIVE.

80
00:04:06,625 --> 00:04:08,709
WE BETTER SEND A MESSENGER
HAWK TO THE FIRE LORD.

81
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:11,625
[HAWK CRIES]

82
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:17,792
A BLACK RIBBON MESSAGE.

83
00:04:17,834 --> 00:04:19,959
THIS IS SO EXCITING.

84
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:20,750
[LAUGHS]

85
00:04:37,917 --> 00:04:40,375
Children: AHH!

86
00:04:40,417 --> 00:04:43,709
HEY, YOU NEED
SOME HELP UNPACKING?

87
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:45,792
SURE, THANKS.
[GRUNTS]

88
00:04:57,083 --> 00:05:00,750
COULD YOU SCOOCH JUST
A LITTLE BIT MORE TO THE...

89
00:05:00,792 --> 00:05:02,500
PERFECT.

90
00:05:02,542 --> 00:05:04,458
[CHILD LAUGHS]

91
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:06,917
HERE...

92
00:05:06,959 --> 00:05:08,333
THIS IS FOR YOU.

93
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:10,417
WHY WOULD I WANT THAT?

94
00:05:10,458 --> 00:05:12,166
I SAW IT AND I THOUGHT
IT WAS PRETTY.

95
00:05:12,208 --> 00:05:14,000
DON'T GIRLS LIKE
STUFF LIKE THIS?

96
00:05:14,041 --> 00:05:16,208
[SCOFFS]: MAYBE STUPID GIRLS.

97
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:17,208
FORGET IT!

98
00:05:27,041 --> 00:05:29,125
WOW, THANKS.

99
00:05:29,166 --> 00:05:30,834
THIS IS SO PRETTY.

100
00:05:30,875 --> 00:05:32,375
NOT AS PRETTY AS YOU ARE.

101
00:05:32,417 --> 00:05:34,458
THAT SHELL'S NOT SO GREAT.

102
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,709
AHEM, SHADE...<i> SHADE.</i>

103
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,208
I THOUGHT SINCE
IT'S SO HOT... HERE.

104
00:05:44,083 --> 00:05:45,000
THANKS.

105
00:05:45,041 --> 00:05:47,709
THIS IS REALLY REFRESHING.

106
00:05:53,083 --> 00:05:55,667
HEY, BEACH BUMS,
WE'RE PLAYING NEXT.

107
00:05:55,709 --> 00:05:57,709
TY LEE, GET
OVER HERE NOW.

108
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:08,291
[GIGGLING]

109
00:06:12,625 --> 00:06:14,959
SEE THAT GIRL WITH
THE SILLY PIGTAILS?

110
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,500
WHEN SHE RUNS
TOWARDS THE BALL...

111
00:06:16,542 --> 00:06:19,000
...THERE'S JUST THE SLIGHTEST
HESITATION OF HER LEFT FOOT.

112
00:06:19,041 --> 00:06:21,959
I'M WILLING TO BET A CHILDHOOD
INJURY HAS WEAKENED HER.

113
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:24,333
KEEP SERVING THE BALL TO HER
LEFT AND WE'LL DESTROY HER

114
00:06:24,375 --> 00:06:25,917
AND THE REST OF HER TEAM.

115
00:06:25,959 --> 00:06:27,542
DISMISSED.

116
00:06:57,417 --> 00:07:00,125
[FIRE CRACKLING]

117
00:07:00,166 --> 00:07:03,208
YES, WE DEFEATED YOU
FOR ALL TIME.

118
00:07:03,250 --> 00:07:06,500
YOU WILL NEVER RISE
FROM THE ASHES OF YOUR
SHAME AND HUMILIATION.

119
00:07:06,542 --> 00:07:10,125
WELL, THAT WAS FUN.

120
00:07:10,166 --> 00:07:11,750
I'M HAVING
A PARTY TONIGHT.

121
00:07:11,792 --> 00:07:13,208
YOU SHOULD COME BY.

122
00:07:13,250 --> 00:07:14,125
SURE...

123
00:07:14,166 --> 00:07:15,458
I LOVE PARTIES.

124
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:17,208
YOUR FRIEND CAN COME, TOO.

125
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:20,041
UH, WHAT ABOUT
ME AND MY BROTHER?

126
00:07:20,083 --> 00:07:21,583
AREN'T YOU GOING TO INVITE US?

127
00:07:21,625 --> 00:07:24,500
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHO WE ARE, DO YOU?

128
00:07:24,542 --> 00:07:26,625
DON'T YOU KNOW WHO WE ARE?

129
00:07:26,667 --> 00:07:28,625
WE'RE CHAN AND RUON-JIAN.

130
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:29,458
YEAH.

131
00:07:31,792 --> 00:07:33,875
BUT FINE, YOU'RE INVITED.

132
00:07:33,917 --> 00:07:35,792
JUST SO YOU KNOW, THOUGH

133
00:07:35,834 --> 00:07:37,500
SOME OF THE MOST IMPORTANT
TEENAGERS IN THE FIRE NATION

134
00:07:37,542 --> 00:07:39,333
ARE GONNA BE AT THIS PARTY SO...

135
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:40,583
TRY AND ACT NORMAL.

136
00:07:40,625 --> 00:07:42,166
WE'LL DO OUR BEST.

137
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:49,709
Zuko: WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL
THOSE GUYS WHO WERE WERE?

138
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,792
Azula: I GUESS I WAS INTRIGUED.

139
00:07:51,834 --> 00:07:53,792
I'M SO USED TO
PEOPLE WORSHIPPING US.

140
00:07:53,834 --> 00:07:55,125
THEY SHOULD.

141
00:07:55,166 --> 00:07:57,375
YES, I KNOW,
AND I LOVE IT.

142
00:07:57,417 --> 00:07:59,417
BUT FOR ONCE,
I JUST WANTED TO SEE

143
00:07:59,458 --> 00:08:01,625
HOW PEOPLE WOULD TREAT US IF
THEY DIDN'T KNOW WHO WE WERE.

144
00:08:01,667 --> 00:08:03,875
LIKE WAVES WASHING AWAY

145
00:08:03,917 --> 00:08:06,208
THE FOOTPRINTS ON THE SAND

146
00:08:06,250 --> 00:08:10,166
EMBER ISLAND GIVES
EVERYONE A CLEAN SLATE.

147
00:08:10,208 --> 00:08:13,083
EMBER ISLAND
REVEALS THE TRUE YOU.

148
00:08:15,875 --> 00:08:17,667
TO THE PARTY.
TO THE PARTY.

149
00:08:17,709 --> 00:08:19,917
[HAWK CRIES]

150
00:08:22,417 --> 00:08:23,250
[CRYING CONTINUES]

151
00:08:27,375 --> 00:08:29,291
[SQUAWKING...]

152
00:08:32,083 --> 00:08:32,750
[HAWK CRIES]

153
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:39,125
[BIRDS CRYING...]

154
00:09:02,792 --> 00:09:04,750
UM... YOU'RE A LITTLE EARLY.

155
00:09:04,792 --> 00:09:06,041
NO ONE'S HERE YET.

156
00:09:06,083 --> 00:09:07,875
I HEARD YOU TELLING SOMEONE

157
00:09:07,917 --> 00:09:09,208
YOU'D BE PARTYING
FROM DUSK TILL DAWN.

158
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:11,709
IT'S DUSK SO WE'RE HERE.

159
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:14,542
BUT THAT'S JUST AN EXPRESSION.

160
00:09:14,583 --> 00:09:16,709
WE ARE THE PERFECT PARTY GUESTS.

161
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:18,792
WE ARRIVE RIGHT ON TIME
BECAUSE WE ARE VERY PUNCTUAL.

162
00:09:24,083 --> 00:09:25,417
Chan: ALL RIGHT, LISTEN,
MY DAD'S AN ADMIRAL.

163
00:09:25,458 --> 00:09:27,000
HE HAS NO IDEA
I'M HAVING THIS PARTY

164
00:09:27,041 --> 00:09:29,083
SO DON'T MESS ANYTHING UP.

165
00:09:30,750 --> 00:09:34,625
THAT'S A SHARP
OUTFIT, CHAN... CAREFUL.

166
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:38,291
YOU COULD PUNCTURE THE HULL
OF AN EMPIRE-CLASS
FIRE NATION BATTLESHIP

167
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:40,667
LEAVING THOUSANDS
TO DROWN AT SEA...

168
00:09:40,709 --> 00:09:44,333
BECAUSE IT'S SO SHARP.

169
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:47,583
UM... THANKS.

170
00:09:52,959 --> 00:09:56,875
HEY, FIRST ONES HERE, HUH?

171
00:09:56,917 --> 00:10:00,458
HE THINKS HE'S SO GREAT.

172
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:03,000
WELL, WHAT DO
YOU THINK OF HIM?

173
00:10:03,041 --> 00:10:04,583
I DON'T HAVE ANY
OPINION ABOUT HIM.

174
00:10:04,625 --> 00:10:06,375
I HARDLY KNOW HIM.

175
00:10:06,417 --> 00:10:08,500
YOU LIKE HIM,
DON'T YOU?
[IRRITATED SIGH]

176
00:10:15,208 --> 00:10:17,083
SO HOW DO YOU KNOW TY LEE?

177
00:10:17,125 --> 00:10:19,208
I MET HER AT THE BEACH TODAY.

178
00:10:19,250 --> 00:10:21,458
SHE WAS PRETTY IMPRESSED
BY A SAND PAGODA
THAT I MADE FOR HER.

179
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:25,125
WELL, I MET HER FIRST.

180
00:10:25,166 --> 00:10:28,500
LOOK, IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHO I MET FIRST
'CAUSE I LIKE YOU ALL.

181
00:10:28,542 --> 00:10:30,625
BUT WHICH ONE OF US
DO YOU<i> LIKE?</i>

182
00:10:30,667 --> 00:10:32,333
YEAH.
TELL US.

183
00:10:32,375 --> 00:10:34,125
I DON'T KNOW, I DON'T KNOW.

184
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:37,250
[ALL GRUNT]

185
00:10:37,291 --> 00:10:38,208
All: OOH.

186
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:39,834
AHH...

187
00:10:39,875 --> 00:10:41,792
OH, I'M GLAD YOU'RE HERE.

188
00:10:41,834 --> 00:10:43,875
THOSE BOYS WON'T
LEAVE ME ALONE.

189
00:10:43,917 --> 00:10:45,917
I GUESS THEY ALL
JUST LIKE ME TOO MUCH.

190
00:10:45,959 --> 00:10:49,083
COME ON, TY LEE,
YOU CAN'T BE THIS IGNORANT.

191
00:10:49,125 --> 00:10:51,166
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

192
00:10:51,208 --> 00:10:54,000
THOSE BOYS ONLY LIKE YOU BECAUSE
YOU MAKE IT SO EASY FOR THEM.

193
00:10:54,041 --> 00:10:56,166
YOU'RE NOT A CHALLENGE-
YOU'RE A TEASE.

194
00:10:56,208 --> 00:10:58,792
IT'S NOT LIKE THEY
ACTUALLY CARE WHO YOU ARE.

195
00:10:58,834 --> 00:11:00,583
[SOBBING]

196
00:11:00,625 --> 00:11:03,667
OK, OK, CALM DOWN.

197
00:11:03,709 --> 00:11:06,792
I DIDN'T MEAN WHAT I SAID.

198
00:11:06,834 --> 00:11:08,917
LOOK, MAYBE I JUST SAID IT
BECAUSE I WAS A LITTLE...

199
00:11:08,959 --> 00:11:09,875
[WHISPERS]: JEALOUS.

200
00:11:09,917 --> 00:11:11,709
WHAT?

201
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:14,000
YOU WERE JEALOUS OF ME?

202
00:11:14,041 --> 00:11:17,917
UM, BUT, YOU'RE THE MOST
BEAUTIFUL, SMARTEST, PERFECT
GIRL IN THE WORLD.

203
00:11:17,959 --> 00:11:19,417
WELL, YOU'RE RIGHT
ABOUT ALL THOSE THINGS.

204
00:11:19,458 --> 00:11:21,375
BUT FOR SOME REASON
WHEN I MEET BOYS

205
00:11:21,417 --> 00:11:23,834
THEY ACT AS IF I'M GOING TO DO
SOMETHING HORRIBLE TO THEM.

206
00:11:23,875 --> 00:11:27,000
[LAUGHS] BUT YOU PROBABLY
WOULD DO SOMETHING
HORRIBLE TO THEM.

207
00:11:27,041 --> 00:11:30,750
I'M SURE THEY'RE
JUST INTIMIDATED BY YOU.

208
00:11:30,792 --> 00:11:33,000
OK, LOOK, IF YOU WANT
A BOY TO LIKE YOU

209
00:11:33,041 --> 00:11:35,000
JUST LOOK AT HIM AND SMILE A LOT

210
00:11:35,041 --> 00:11:38,041
AND LAUGH AT EVERYTHING HE SAYS
EVEN IF IT'S NOT FUNNY.

211
00:11:38,083 --> 00:11:42,458
WELL, THAT SOUNDS
REALLY SHALLOW AND STUPID.

212
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:43,625
LET'S TRY IT.

213
00:11:43,667 --> 00:11:45,291
OK.

214
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:47,291
[AS BOY]: "HEY, THERE,
SWEET SUGAR CAKES.

215
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:49,667
HOW YA LIKIN' THIS PARTY?"

216
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:52,208
[LAUGHS GIDDILY]

217
00:11:52,250 --> 00:11:53,750
[SILENCE]

218
00:11:53,792 --> 00:11:56,959
Mai: I'M BORED.
Zuko: I KNOW.

219
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,375
I'M HUNGRY.
SO WHAT?

220
00:11:59,417 --> 00:12:01,333
SO FIND ME SOME FOOD.

221
00:12:01,375 --> 00:12:02,291
SURE.

222
00:12:05,625 --> 00:12:08,250
CHAN, I'M READY FOR
A TOUR OF THE HOUSE.

223
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:15,000
Chan: IS THIS YOUR FIRST TIME
ON EMBER ISLAND?

224
00:12:15,041 --> 00:12:17,542
Azula: NO, I USED TO
COME HERE YEARS AGO.

225
00:12:17,583 --> 00:12:20,125
IT'S A GREAT PLACE
IF YOU LIKE SAND.

226
00:12:20,166 --> 00:12:22,959
[LAUGHING]

227
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:26,834
YEAH, IT'S LIKE,
"WELCOME TO SANDY LAND."

228
00:12:26,875 --> 00:12:28,959
[BOTH LAUGH]

229
00:12:31,583 --> 00:12:35,208
YOUR ARMS LOOK SO STRONG.

230
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:37,583
YEAH, I KNOW.

231
00:12:41,083 --> 00:12:42,959
YOU'RE PRETTY.

232
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,375
[SWEETLY]: TOGETHER,
YOU AND I WILL BE...

233
00:12:45,417 --> 00:12:48,125
[FIRMLY]: THE STRONGEST COUPLE
IN THE ENTIRE WORLD.

234
00:12:48,166 --> 00:12:49,542
WE WILL DOMINATE THE EARTH!

235
00:12:54,041 --> 00:12:57,375
UH... I GOTTA GO.

236
00:13:08,083 --> 00:13:10,250
HEY, WATCH IT.

237
00:13:10,291 --> 00:13:12,000
THAT FOOD WAS FOR
MY CRANKY GIRLFRIEND.

238
00:13:17,625 --> 00:13:18,583
WHOA...

239
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:21,667
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

240
00:13:21,709 --> 00:13:23,333
STOP TALKING TO MY GIRLFRIEND.

241
00:13:23,375 --> 00:13:25,792
RELAX, IT'S JUST A PARTY.

242
00:13:25,834 --> 00:13:26,834
UH!

243
00:13:28,291 --> 00:13:31,125
ZUKO, WHAT IS WRONG
WITH YOU?

244
00:13:31,166 --> 00:13:32,875
WHAT'S WRONG WITH ME?

245
00:13:32,917 --> 00:13:34,500
YOUR TEMPER'S
OUT OF CONTROL.

246
00:13:34,542 --> 00:13:36,500
YOU BLOW UP OVER
EVERY LITTLE THING.

247
00:13:36,542 --> 00:13:39,542
YOU'RE SO IMPATIENT AND
HOT-HEADED AND ANGRY.

248
00:13:39,583 --> 00:13:42,333
WELL, AT LEAST
I FEEL SOMETHING...
AS OPPOSED TO YOU.

249
00:13:42,375 --> 00:13:43,875
YOU HAVE NO PASSION
FOR ANYTHING.

250
00:13:43,917 --> 00:13:46,625
YOU'RE JUST A BIG BLAH.

251
00:13:46,667 --> 00:13:49,000
IT'S OVER, ZUKO.

252
00:13:49,041 --> 00:13:50,709
WE'RE DONE.

253
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:52,917
WHO BROKE MY NANA'S VASE?

254
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:56,208
THAT'S IT,
YOU'RE OUT OF HERE.

255
00:13:56,250 --> 00:13:58,000
I WAS JUST LEAVING.

256
00:13:58,041 --> 00:14:00,917
HAVE FUN BY YOURSELF,
LOSER BOY.

257
00:14:00,959 --> 00:14:02,166
NICE.

258
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:12,667
[WAVES GENTLY ROLL]

259
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:24,959
[CHILDREN SHRIEKING]

260
00:14:30,041 --> 00:14:31,959
[BIRD SINGS]

261
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:38,041
[BABY CRIES]

262
00:15:09,375 --> 00:15:11,208
[BABY LAUGHS]

263
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:26,458
[METALLIC CLANKING]

264
00:15:29,208 --> 00:15:31,375
GUYS, YOU'RE ALL GONNA
THINK I'M CRAZY

265
00:15:31,417 --> 00:15:33,000
BUT IT FEELS LIKE
A METAL MAN IS COMING.

266
00:15:33,041 --> 00:15:36,417
[GROANS]

267
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:49,333
[GRUNTS]

268
00:15:51,917 --> 00:15:52,750
[GROANS]

269
00:15:54,083 --> 00:15:55,125
[ALL SCREAM]

270
00:16:08,875 --> 00:16:09,875
[APPA ROARS]

271
00:16:19,875 --> 00:16:21,500
Azula: I THOUGHT
I'D FIND YOU HERE.

272
00:16:21,542 --> 00:16:25,375
THOSE SUMMERS WE SPENT
HERE SEEM SO LONG AGO.

273
00:16:25,417 --> 00:16:28,166
SO MUCH HAS CHANGED.

274
00:16:28,208 --> 00:16:29,709
COME DOWN TO THE
BEACH WITH ME.

275
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:32,083
COME ON,
THIS PLACE IS DEPRESSING.

276
00:16:43,166 --> 00:16:45,375
HEY...

277
00:16:45,417 --> 00:16:47,083
WHERE'S YOUR NEW BOYFRIEND?

278
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:53,166
ARE YOU COLD?

279
00:16:53,208 --> 00:16:55,834
I'M FREEZING.

280
00:16:55,875 --> 00:16:57,750
I'LL MAKE A FIRE.

281
00:16:57,792 --> 00:17:01,083
Zuko: THERE'S PLENTY OF
STUFF TO BURN IN THERE.

282
00:17:01,125 --> 00:17:01,875
[GROWLS]

283
00:17:05,125 --> 00:17:07,041
THIS IS CRAZY.

284
00:17:07,083 --> 00:17:09,250
HOW CAN WE BEAT A GUY WHO BLOWS
THINGS UP WITH HIS MIND?

285
00:17:09,291 --> 00:17:10,375
WE CAN.

286
00:17:10,417 --> 00:17:11,750
JUMP ON APPA.

287
00:17:11,792 --> 00:17:12,583
I'LL TRY TO DISTRACT HIM.

288
00:17:27,875 --> 00:17:30,083
[PANTING]

289
00:17:33,208 --> 00:17:36,083
[HEAVY FOOTSTEPS THUD]

290
00:17:43,917 --> 00:17:46,417
[HEAVY FOOTSTEPS CONTINUE]

291
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:29,208
[APPA GROWLS]

292
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:31,959
[SIGH]: I'M OK.

293
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,125
WELL, THAT WAS RANDOM.

294
00:18:33,166 --> 00:18:34,792
I DON'T THINK SO.

295
00:18:34,834 --> 00:18:37,458
I GET THE FEELING
HE KNOWS WHO WE ARE.

296
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:40,208
[FIRE CRACKLING]

297
00:18:42,709 --> 00:18:44,667
Ty Lee: WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

298
00:18:44,709 --> 00:18:46,250
WHAT DOES IT LOOK
LIKE I'M DOING.

299
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:49,041
BUT IT'S A PAINTING
OF YOUR FAMILY.

300
00:18:49,083 --> 00:18:50,208
YOU THINK I CARE?

301
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:51,792
I THINK YOU DO.

302
00:18:51,834 --> 00:18:55,250
YOU DON'T KNOW ME, SO WHY DON'T
YOU JUST MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS?

303
00:18:55,291 --> 00:18:57,166
AH, I KNOW YOU.

304
00:18:57,208 --> 00:18:59,375
NO, YOU DON'T.

305
00:18:59,417 --> 00:19:01,000
YOU'RE STUCK IN YOUR
LITTLE TY LEE WORLD

306
00:19:01,041 --> 00:19:03,083
WHERE EVERYTHING'S
GREAT ALL THE TIME.

307
00:19:03,125 --> 00:19:05,000
ZUKO, LEAVE HER ALONE.

308
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:06,500
[MOCKING]: I'M SO PRETTY,
LOOK AT ME.

309
00:19:06,542 --> 00:19:08,083
I CAN WALK ON MY HANDS, WHOO!

310
00:19:11,542 --> 00:19:13,041
CIRCUS FREAK.

311
00:19:13,083 --> 00:19:15,000
[LAUGHS]

312
00:19:15,041 --> 00:19:17,041
YES, I'M A CIRCUS FREAK.

313
00:19:17,083 --> 00:19:19,417
GO AHEAD AND LAUGH
ALL YOU WANT.

314
00:19:19,458 --> 00:19:21,291
YOU WANNA KNOW WHY
I JOINED THE CIRCUS?

315
00:19:21,333 --> 00:19:23,250
HERE WE GO.

316
00:19:23,291 --> 00:19:25,792
Ty Lee: DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT MY HOME LIFE WAS LIKE

317
00:19:25,834 --> 00:19:27,208
GROWING UP WITH SIX SISTERS

318
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:29,834
WHO LOOK EXACTLY LIKE ME?

319
00:19:29,875 --> 00:19:32,000
IT WAS LIKE,
I DIDN'T EVEN HAVE MY OWN NAME.

320
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:33,959
I JOINED THE CIRCUS BECAUSE

321
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,125
I WAS SCARED OF SPENDING
THE REST OF MY LIFE

322
00:19:36,166 --> 00:19:38,166
AS PART OF A MATCHED SET.

323
00:19:38,208 --> 00:19:39,959
AT LEAST, I'M DIFFERENT NOW.

324
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,959
CIRCUS FREAK IS A COMPLIMENT.

325
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:46,125
GUESS THAT EXPLAINS WHY YOU
NEED 10 BOYFRIENDS, TOO.

326
00:19:46,166 --> 00:19:48,125
I'M SORRY, WHAT?

327
00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:50,083
ATTENTION ISSUES?

328
00:19:50,125 --> 00:19:51,917
YOU COULDN'T GET ENOUGH
ATTENTION WHEN YOU WERE A KID

329
00:19:51,959 --> 00:19:54,333
SO YOU'RE TRYING
TO MAKE UP FOR IT NOW.

330
00:19:54,375 --> 00:19:57,542
WELL, WHAT'S YOUR EXCUSE, MAI?

331
00:19:57,583 --> 00:19:59,875
YOU WERE AN ONLY CHILD
FOR 15 YEARS.

332
00:19:59,917 --> 00:20:01,583
BUT EVEN WITH ALL THAT ATTENTION

333
00:20:01,625 --> 00:20:04,709
YOUR AURA IS THIS
DINGY, PASTY, GRAY...

334
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:07,250
I DON'T BELIEVE IN AURAS.

335
00:20:07,291 --> 00:20:09,875
YEAH, YOU DON'T
BELIEVE IN ANYTHING.

336
00:20:09,917 --> 00:20:13,792
OH, WELL, I'M SORRY
I CAN'T BE AS HIGH-STRUNG
AND CRAZY AS THE REST OF YOU.

337
00:20:13,834 --> 00:20:15,667
Zuko: I'M SORRY, TOO.

338
00:20:15,709 --> 00:20:18,834
I WISH YOU WOULD BE
HIGH-STRUNG AND CRAZY FOR ONCE

339
00:20:18,875 --> 00:20:20,709
INSTEAD OF KEEPING ALL YOUR
FEELINGS BOTTLED UP INSIDE.

340
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:22,583
SHE JUST CALLED YOUR AURA DINGY.

341
00:20:22,625 --> 00:20:23,917
ARE YOU GONNA TAKE THAT?

342
00:20:23,959 --> 00:20:25,917
WHAT DO YOU WANT FROM ME?

343
00:20:25,959 --> 00:20:29,208
YOU WANT A TEARY CONFESSION
ABOUT HOW HARD MY CHILDHOOD WAS?

344
00:20:29,250 --> 00:20:31,083
WELL, IT WASN'T.

345
00:20:31,125 --> 00:20:33,625
I WAS A RICH ONLY CHILD
WHO GOT ANYTHING I WANTED

346
00:20:33,667 --> 00:20:36,083
AS LONG AS I BEHAVED...

347
00:20:36,125 --> 00:20:38,333
...AND SAT STILL

348
00:20:38,375 --> 00:20:41,208
AND DIDN'T SPEAK
UNLESS SPOKEN TO.

349
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:44,083
MY MOTHER SAID I HAD
TO KEEP OUT OF TROUBLE.

350
00:20:44,125 --> 00:20:46,166
WE HAD MY DAD'S POLITICAL
CAREER TO THINK ABOUT.

351
00:20:46,208 --> 00:20:48,291
Azula: WELL, THAT'S IT, THEN.

352
00:20:48,333 --> 00:20:51,208
YOU HAD A CONTROLLING MOTHER
WHO HAD CERTAIN EXPECTATIONS

353
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:53,083
AND IF YOU STRAYED FROM THEM
YOU WERE SHUT DOWN.

354
00:20:53,125 --> 00:20:55,500
THAT'S WHY YOU'RE AFRAID
TO CARE ABOUT ANYTHING

355
00:20:55,542 --> 00:20:56,959
AND WHY YOU CAN'T
EXPRESS YOURSELF.

356
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,166
YOU WANT ME TO EXPRESS MYSELF?

357
00:20:59,208 --> 00:21:00,041
LEAVE ME ALONE!

358
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:05,166
I LIKE IT WHEN YOU
EXPRESS YOURSELF.

359
00:21:05,208 --> 00:21:06,208
DON'T TOUCH ME.

360
00:21:06,250 --> 00:21:08,625
I'M STILL MAD AT YOU.

361
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:12,166
MY LIFE HASN'T BEEN
THAT EASY, EITHER, MAI.

362
00:21:12,208 --> 00:21:14,667
WHATEVER- THAT DOESN'T EXCUSE
THE WAY YOU'VE BEEN ACTING.

363
00:21:14,709 --> 00:21:16,458
Ty Lee: CALM DOWN, YOU GUYS.

364
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:19,000
THIS MUCH NEGATIVE ENERGY
IS BAD FOR YOUR SKIN.

365
00:21:19,041 --> 00:21:20,458
YOU'LL TOTALLY BREAK OUT.

366
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,083
Zuko: BAD SKIN?

367
00:21:22,125 --> 00:21:24,125
NORMAL TEENAGERS WORRY
ABOUT BAD SKIN.

368
00:21:24,166 --> 00:21:26,208
I DON'T HAVE THAT LUXURY.

369
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:29,583
MY FATHER DECIDED TO TEACH ME
A PERMANENT LESSON ON MY FACE.

370
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:32,000
SORRY, ZUKO, I...

371
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:34,959
FOR SO LONG, I THOUGHT
THAT IF MY DAD ACCEPTED ME,
I'D BE HAPPY.

372
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,041
I'M BACK HOME, NOW.

373
00:21:36,083 --> 00:21:37,291
MY DAD TALKS TO ME.

374
00:21:37,333 --> 00:21:39,709
HUH, HE EVEN THINKS I'M A HERO.

375
00:21:39,750 --> 00:21:41,250
EVERYTHING SHOULD
BE PERFECT, RIGHT?

376
00:21:41,291 --> 00:21:43,750
I SHOULD BE HAPPY NOW,
BUT I'M NOT.

377
00:21:43,792 --> 00:21:46,417
I'M ANGRIER THAN EVER
AND I DON'T KNOW WHY.

378
00:21:46,458 --> 00:21:48,583
THERE'S A SIMPLE QUESTION
YOU NEED TO ANSWER THEN.

379
00:21:48,625 --> 00:21:50,208
WHO ARE YOU ANGRY AT?

380
00:21:50,250 --> 00:21:53,083
NO ONE,
I'M JUST ANGRY.

381
00:21:53,125 --> 00:21:55,625
YEAH, WHO ARE YOU
ANGRY AT, ZUKO?

382
00:21:55,667 --> 00:21:58,458
EVERYONE... I DON'T KNOW.

383
00:21:58,500 --> 00:21:59,458
IS IT DAD?

384
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:01,208
NO, NO.

385
00:22:01,250 --> 00:22:02,208
YOUR UNCLE?
ME?

386
00:22:02,250 --> 00:22:04,250
NO, NO... NO, NO.

387
00:22:04,291 --> 00:22:05,542
THEN WHO?

388
00:22:05,583 --> 00:22:06,917
WHO ARE YOU ANGRY AT?

389
00:22:06,959 --> 00:22:08,208
ANSWER THE QUESTION, ZUKO.

390
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:09,750
Ty Lee: TALK TO US.

391
00:22:09,792 --> 00:22:11,125
Mai: COME ON,
ANSWER THE QUESTION.

392
00:22:11,166 --> 00:22:12,250
Azula: COME ON, ANSWER IT.

393
00:22:12,291 --> 00:22:14,542
Zuko: I'M ANGRY AT MYSELF.

394
00:22:19,542 --> 00:22:20,875
Azula: WHY?

395
00:22:20,917 --> 00:22:23,458
BECAUSE I'M CONFUSED.

396
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:25,375
BECAUSE I'M NOT SURE
I KNOW THE DIFFERENCE

397
00:22:25,417 --> 00:22:27,041
BETWEEN RIGHT
AND WRONG ANYMORE.

398
00:22:27,083 --> 00:22:28,500
YOU'RE PATHETIC.

399
00:22:28,542 --> 00:22:31,458
Mai: I KNOW ONE THING
I CARE ABOUT...

400
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:33,166
I CARE ABOUT YOU.

401
00:22:35,625 --> 00:22:37,375
[LONE HAND CLAP]

402
00:22:37,417 --> 00:22:40,375
WELL, THOSE WERE WONDERFUL
PERFORMANCES, EVERYONE.

403
00:22:40,417 --> 00:22:43,458
I GUESS YOU WOULDN'T
UNDERSTAND, WOULD YOU, AZULA

404
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:45,250
BECAUSE YOU'RE
JUST<i> SO</i> PERFECT.

405
00:22:45,291 --> 00:22:47,542
WELL, YES, I GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT.

406
00:22:47,583 --> 00:22:50,083
I DON'T HAVE SOB STORIES
LIKE ALL OF YOU.

407
00:22:50,125 --> 00:22:52,917
I COULD SIT HERE
AND COMPLAIN HOW OUR MOM
LIKED ZUKO MORE THAN ME

408
00:22:52,959 --> 00:22:55,625
BUT I DON'T REALLY CARE.

409
00:22:55,667 --> 00:22:57,250
MY OWN MOTHER...

410
00:22:57,291 --> 00:22:59,125
THOUGHT I WAS A MONSTER.

411
00:23:02,125 --> 00:23:06,291
SHE WAS RIGHT, OF COURSE,
BUT IT STILL HURT.

412
00:23:06,333 --> 00:23:08,750
Ty Lee: WHAT LO AND LI
SAID CAME TRUE.

413
00:23:08,792 --> 00:23:10,709
THE BEACH DID HELP US
LEARN ABOUT OURSELVES.

414
00:23:10,750 --> 00:23:13,125
I FEEL ALL SMOOTHED.

415
00:23:13,166 --> 00:23:15,000
I'LL ALWAYS REMEMBER THIS.

416
00:23:15,041 --> 00:23:17,917
YOU KNOW WHAT WOULD MAKE
THIS TRIP REALLY MEMORABLE?

417
00:23:22,083 --> 00:23:24,417
WE'VE GOT SOME BAD NEWS, CHAN.

418
00:23:24,458 --> 00:23:25,583
PARTY'S OVER.

419
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:29,125
[SCREAMING]

420
00:23:29,166 --> 00:23:30,166
[GRUNTS]

421
00:23:39,875 --> 00:23:40,750
[CRYING LOUDLY]

422
00:23:51,250 --> 00:23:52,959
♪

423
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,917
♪ [MEN VOCALIZING
RHYTHMICALLY] ♪
